


                    TINE 2.0 RELEASENOTES
                    
Release:     Collin (2013.10)
Last change: 2013-10-16

For a comprehensive list of user-related releasenotes with screenshots see
the Tine 2.0 Wiki at http://www.tine20.org/wiki/index.php/Releases/Collin

Contents
--
1. PHP module requirements / proposals
2. ActiveDirectory support
3. Login CAPTCHA support
4. OwnCloud client support

1. PHP module requirements / proposals
-----------------

- php module intl is recommended (for calendar notifications)
- php module hash is now marked as required

2. ActiveDirectory support
-----------------

Tine 2.0 now supports ActiveDirectory as accounts backend. It is possible
to configure that in the setup.

more information: https://forge.tine20.org/mantisbt/view.php?id=2756

3. Login CAPTCHA support
-----------------

It is now possible to show a CAPTCHA on the login page when a user enters
wrong credentials multiple times. This is configurable in the config.inc.php.

more information: https://forge.tine20.org/mantisbt/view.php?id=8484

4. OwnCloud client support
-----------------

OwnCloud clients are now able to connect to a Tine 2.0 server.

more information: https://www.tine20.org/wiki/index.php/Admins/Synchronisation/Owncloud
